Corrupt eThekwini Municipality officials are about to face the music. Courtesy #DStv403 DURBAN - eThekwini City Manager, Sipho Nzuza, has been released on R50, 000 bail. Nzuza was arrested by the Hawks on Tuesday morning. He is facing charges of fraud and corruption totalling around R430-million. READ: eThekwini promises mall will benefit community Nzuza is expected back in court on 16 April. It's related to the Durban Solid Waste tender. Around 300-people have been investigated, and some cases date back to 2003.